    h1 BULLDOZERS AND BAND-AIDS

    p 
      | Successive government policies have, as one submission put it, 
      em “cut down trees with one hand and picked up injured koalas with the other”.

    p
      | For instance, the <em>
      +link('Planning Policy for Koala Habitat 2019', 'https://www.legislation.nsw.gov.au/view/html/inforce/current/epi-2019-0658')
      | </em> aimed to “reverse the current trend of koala population decline”, yet it exempted major state developments from koala-related obligations. It also exempted projects smaller than 1 ha, ignoring the cumulative impact of many small developments over time.
      | Further, under the 
      +link('Local Land Services Act 2013', 'https://www.legislation.nsw.gov.au/view/html/inforce/current/act-2013-051')
      |  landowners were merely required to “self-assess” koala habitat before clearing land.
